# .sinemacula/ tracking policy (allowlist v1)
#
# Managed by /build:init and the session:start hook. Do NOT remove the
# `*` catch-all or the sentinel comment above — the session-start sync hook
# uses them to detect this format and apply migrations from older versions.
#
# Why allowlist? Plugins write into .sinemacula/ automatically (workflow
# state, audit reports, model-routing snapshots, etc.). Deny-by-default
# means future plugin updates can never accidentally commit new artefacts;
# only the explicit allowlist below gets through.
#
# To track an additional file, add an explicit `!<path>` allow-entry below
# (and commit it). To opt a directory out of tracking, remove its
# `!<path>` entry. Never edit the `*` line.

# Deny everything by default
*

# Allow team-shared policy + config (always tracked)
!.gitignore
!config.toml
!release-allowlist.json

# Allow visual-regression baselines — shared so every engineer compares
# against the same reference set. Remove these two lines to make baselines
# per-machine.
!browser-qa/
!browser-qa/**
